.TH "hv_register_block_invalidate" 9 "hv_register_block_invalidate" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hv_register_block_invalidate \- Invoked when a config block invalidation arrives from the back-end driver.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" hv_register_block_invalidate
.BI "(struct pci_dev *pdev "  ","
.BI "void *context "  ","
.BI "void (*block_invalidate)(void *context, u64 block_mask) "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
The PCI driver's representation for this device.
.IP "context" 12
Identifies the device.
.IP "block_invalidate" 12
Identifies all of the blocks being invalidated.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, -errno on failure
